## Phase 4: Models and build

### Step 4a: Add new blocks to section model filters

Use `bash` tool (NOT haiku) with this exact node command — no LLM needed for JSON array edits:

```bash
node -e "
const fs = require('fs');
const f = 'models/_section.json';
const j = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(f,'utf8'));
const add = ['video-scrub','photo-effect','image-table'];
const filters = j.filters ?? j;
const arr = Array.isArray(filters) ? filters : (filters.components ?? []);
add.forEach(id => { if (!arr.includes(id)) arr.push(id); });
if (Array.isArray(filters)) { j.filters = arr; } else { filters.components = arr; }
fs.writeFileSync(f, JSON.stringify(j, null, 2));
console.log('added:', add.join(', '));
"
```

